  "market_context": "ES 5-minute chart showing price action with multiple swing highs lined up overhead and equal lows at the bottom. A higher-time-frame failure swing exists overhead where a prior high was not taken out before reversal.",
  "key_observation": "Equal lows just got swept into a gap, wiping out sellside liquidity and creating high resistance liquidity below. Above price sit failure-swing highs (lower highs that never swept the prior high) acting as low resistance liquidity draws.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Scan the chart and notice multiple highs lined up overhead, with one high that failed to take out a prior high — a higher time frame failure swing (low resistance liquidity).",
    "Step 2: Look below price and identify equal lows that were just swept into a fair value gap, creating high resistance liquidity beneath.",
    "Step 3: Anticipate a change in state of delivery from the swept low, expecting price to trade up and take out the failure-swing highs as the low resistance liquidity target.",
    "Step 4: Confirm by watching price deliver away from the swept low toward those overhead failure swings."
  ],
  "outcome": "Analyst notes 'there we go' as price delivers up off the swept lows toward the failure-swing highs, validating the read.",
  "lessons": "Target failure swings (low resistance liquidity) and keep swept/high resistance liquidity on your side as protection. After a sweep of equal lows into a gap, anticipate a state-of-delivery shift toward overhead unswept highs.",
